HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 853
By Butler
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Eddie Cook of Fentress County
upon his induction into the Tennessee School
Boards Association Quarter Century Club.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Eddie Cook, who has demonstrated an
unwavering commitment to education through his service on the Fentress County Board of
Education; and
WHEREAS, for his dedication to the betterment of those entrusted to him, the
Tennessee School Boards Association (TSBA) honored Mr. Cook in November of 2025 by
inducting him into the TSBA Quarter Century Club; and
WHEREAS, Eddie Cook has earned this honor by serving on his local school board for
twenty-five years, demonstrating his leadership through his consistent concern and boundless
insight; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Cook's constant devotion to education aligns with TSBA's mission to
assist school boards in effectively governing school districts and helping members reach their
highest potential; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor Eddie Cook upon his induction into the Tennessee School
Boards Association Quarter Century Club and commend his role in fostering education and
strengthening communities through his leadership.
